originalText.text: This laundromat has the most reasonable prices for their machines in the area!!! I personally always want to avoid using a laundry card, but you truly can’t beat the prices from other competitors nearby. The attendant as well as who I believe may be management, both were very helpful from the moment I walked through the door, to answering any questions I had, big or small. They have a cold drinks vending machine. Plenty of washing machines. The only thing I wish they had was MORE dryers. But find a day in the week where it’s not so crowded and you should be fine!! 5/5 stars.

originalText.text: Open 24 hours, 7 days a week (key to the front door is unconfirmed rumor) and depending on hour and day,  heavily used or not at all. The lighting is dim, plenty of washers and dryers but not all in working order. Pay attention to the post-it notes!  Restroom available but accessible to customers, strictly the mgmt's call. (The posted sign says Out of Order.) Small post-its note symptoms and very often a diagnosis. The cards used to activate all machines are unwieldy to use, do not always work and there is not much you can do about it. When I complained to the service desk that an overhead a/c unit had leaked discolored water all over my white dress shirt, the manager then on duty looked at me blankly and walked away muttering something in Spanish. Better get used to the idea that for Mexican families with many children what you regard as your local laundromat at will at times double as a playground and if that means unruly children using laundry carts as bumper cars -- or two boys play-fighting with sticks, you best get out of the way. If the music is too loud it is to dissuade the homeless from sleeping over.  Twilight Zone experiences here abound.
